{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01S4E3Gcwgc32MbmUHebdypf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it. In `exp2reg`, when the expression is a local variable with pending jumps (i.e. `!i` where `i` is a local), the function passes the local's register as the destination of the boolean materialization, clobbering the local.\n\nROOT CAUSE: `src/be_code.c:455-472` (`exp2reg`). When `e` is `ETLOCAL` (e.g. the operand `i` in `!i`), `var2reg` returns the local's register (line 443) without changing `e->type` to `ETREG`. The branch `if (hasjump(e))` then sets `reg = e->v.idx` (line 462) and emits `code_bool(finfo, reg, …)` at lines 464–465. Because `reg` is the local variable's slot, the `LDBOOL` instructions overwrite the local. So in `def f(i) var j = !i; return i end`, after evaluating `!i` the parameter `i` has been replaced by the boolean result, and `f(1)` returns `false`.\n\nLOCAL FIX: In `exp2reg`, if `hasjump(e)` and the source isn't a fresh temporary (i.e. `e->type` is `ETLOCAL`/`ETCONST`, or equivalently `reg < finfo->freereg` and it's not an `ETREG`), allocate a new destination register and use it instead of the local's slot. Concretely, before line 462:\n```c\nif (e->type != ETREG) {\n    reg = (dst >= 0 && dst < finfo->freereg) ? dst : be_code_allocregs(finfo, 1);\n} else {\n    reg = e->v.idx;\n}\n```\nand use that `reg` for the subsequent `code_bool` calls. This ensures the boolean materialization writes to a temp, never to a named local.\n\nGLOBAL FIX: The bug class is \"code generator treats `ETLOCAL`/`ETCONST` operand registers as writable scratch.\" Enforce a single invariant throughout `be_code.c`: a destination register must always be `ETREG` (a freshly owned temp at/above `finfo->freereg`). Centralize this with a helper like `exp2anyreg_writable(e)` that, for any non-`ETREG` expression, materializes the value into a newly allocated register and sets `e->type = ETREG` before any opcode that mutates the register is emitted. Audit `unaryexp`, `binaryexp`, `exp2reg`'s jump-materialization path, and `code_suffix` to use it. Add an assertion in `codeABC`/`codeABx` that any register written as the `A` operand is either `>= finfo->freereg-allocated` or explicitly the assignment target — catching this whole family of \"stomped a local\" bugs at compile time of the bytecode."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2360,"cache_read_input_tokens":32926,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2360},"output_tokens":53,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"129de35a-2b42-496c-bc3b-0bf3b6d71c50","uuid":"bca2aa8c-13dc-4301-83e4-dfd7de61aa85"}
